# Composites workshop

This is a very new outreach event which involves making composites out of Fiber glass and Foam core. The students will make the composite and then test it after drying in comparasin to plain foam core to see the difference in strength. This event is always paired with a presentation and may be paired with a lab tour. This event needs to either be split up into two days or needs 2+ hours to allow the composites to properly dry for testing. 

## Items needed

To run a composities workshop you will need:

- 2x8 inch cut out fiberglass sheets (2 per group)
- 2x8 inch cut out foam core (2 per group)
- 30 minute Epoxy (resin + hardner)
- Peel ply (1 Sheet per group)
- Trash bags (1 per group)
- Table cloths
- Scissors
- Gloves
- Scale
- Popsicle sticks / Tool to mix & spread the epoxy
- Cups (for mixing epoxy, need 1 cup per group)
- Composite samples
- Composite sample tester
- Everything needed from [Presentations](#Presentations)

## Running the event

### Prep for the event

This event needs a significant amount of prep, before running the event you must cut out all of the fiberglass, foamcore and peel ply sections. To cut out the fiberglass please repeat the following steps:

1. **Prepare Fiberglass:** Stretch out fiberglass fully so size does not change as you are cutting
2. **Prepare cut lines:** Using a ruler and a sharpie draw out 2x8 inch grids of the fiber glass.
3. **Cutting Preperation:** Over the grid lines made, cover in blue tape
4. **Cutting the fiberglass:** Cut along the blue tape to get the 2x8 samples

This will allow you to get consistent fiberglass samples with clean edges. Without the blue tape cutting the fiberglass will be much more challenging.

### At the event

**Day 1:**

Once at the event you will start by giving the presentation on composites and what our club does. After the presentation pass around the box of gloves and make sure every student gets a pair of gloves. Group students up into groups of 2-3 depending on how many samples you have and then pass out a trashbag to every group (this is used to keep the table clean). Then, hand out the peel ply, fiberglass sheets and foam core. 

After every group has all the required materials start preparing epoxy for each group. Each group will need roughly 10 grams of epoxy. Hand out the cups once mixed and tell them to coat the fiberglass with epoxy on the peel ply. After they have coated one side they will flip over the sample and put the other sheet of fiberglass on the other side. 

Once completed, the samples will need a minimum of 1 hour to cure before the samples can be tested. If this event is being run in one day you can give another presentation in this time or a run a different event. 

**Day 2**

The second day of this event will be testing the composites they made in the last session. Start by quizzing them to see if they know what the fiber and the matrix are and if they think their composite sample will be stronger than the basic foam core. 

Hand the samples back to the groups who made them as well as a plain foam core sample. Pass around the composite testing device and have them test each piece to see if their sample is any stronger. After everyone has finished do a quick Q&A about composites and our club. Clean up and throw out samples and the event is done!

**Note:** In the past the second day has been combined with a lab tour